               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18370918-name-1261" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18370918-name-1261" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18370918-name-1261" type="surname" value="BEETON"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18370918-name-1261" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>JOHN BEETON</persName>
                  </hi>. I am in the employ Messrs. Ballard. On the 25th of August I was near St. George's Church, Southwark, at three o'clock in the afternoon—a female said my pocket was picked—I turned round and saw the prisoner—he took my handkerchief out of his pocket and gave it to me, when I charged him with picking my pocket—he turned his head and saw me when I was about four yards from him, and he took it out and gave him to an officer.</p>
               <p>
